body:
The market can stay irrational longer than you can stay solvent.    I dumped tesla when it approached ford levels of valuation.   I just didn't see it surpassing Ford.   Here we are, the stock market is making them the single largest car company in the world.

Yes they are more.  Herp so is Toyota, Hyundai, Volvo, and VW.   They're much more than car companies too.   

&amp;#x200B;

Let's see where it goes, but I'm going to stay away from this.  Enjoy the ride folks, it's been fun to watch everyone be so happy.

&amp;#x200B;

However let's not let emotion get the better of us.  People who say: "you just don't understand Tesla like I do" are just using confirmation bias to justify their positions.   

&amp;#x200B;

Great company with great engineers and great leadership.  All that is absolutely true.   Good diversity in their positions beyond just cars is true as well.   None of this justifies them as a top ten company in the world.
